						}
					}
				},
				{
					"id": "forefoot",
					"choice_name": "Forefoot",
					"table_name": "Forefoot",
					"slots": 1,
					"hit_penalty": -5,
					"description": "Roll randomly to determine if the left or right leg or foot is hit (targeted attacks permit the attacker to choose). Crippling damage does not necessarily cause a four-legged creature to fall. If it successfully makes a roll against DX-3, it retains its footing. It may not attack with a wounded foreleg, nor may it attack with\nthe other foreleg unless it can fly, or rear onto its hind legs like a bear. In the latter case, it attacks at -3 and does only half damage. With a\nwounded hind leg, the animal attacks at -3, but does normal damage. Speed in either case is reduced by 3",
					"calc": {
						"roll_range": "14",
